Class RectStroke

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JSONSerializable<Stroke>, Comparable<CaliSmallElement>

    public class RectStroke
extends Stroke
    A rounded rect stroke.

    RectStroke's are used whenever a Scrap's border have been "rectified" by the BubbleMenu's shrinkWrapped button.

    Author:
    Michele Bonazza

      • RectStroke

        public RectStroke(Stroke copyStyleFrom,
          RectF borders,
          float radius)
        Creates a new rect stroke using the same style as the argument Stroke, whose outer borders will be aligned to the argument borders and having its corners rounded by the argument radius.
        Parameters:
        copyStyleFrom - the stroke from which style will be copied
        borders - the outer borders for this stroke
        radius - the radius (as would be used in Path.addRoundRect(RectF, float, float, android.graphics.Path.Direction) ) for the corners
